@scenario_hash:1f50e4f839dde04d
Scenario: An adopter lands on the shopsystem-docs entry document and identifies framework, prerequisites, and the next step
  Given the shopsystem-docs BC repository is published at https://github.com/dstengle/shopsystem-docs
  And an adopter has Docker installed and a GitHub account but no prior knowledge of the shopsystem framework
  When the adopter opens the repository's entry document (README.md or a designated entry markdown file) in a browser
  Then the entry document names the shopsystem framework and states in one sentence what it is for
  And the entry document enumerates the prerequisites the adopter needs (Docker, a GitHub account)
  And the entry document points to exactly one next step (a named markdown file or a named first command) the adopter takes to begin bootstrapping their own product
